1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION expressing Kentucky's support for the Crisis
2 Recovery Support Network coordinated by the Southern Regional Education Board,
3 expressing support for Kentucky's participation in the network, and recognizing the
4 network as a trusted support for Kentucky schools, districts, and postsecondary
5 institutions to know they may call upon if the need arises.
6 WHEREAS, after natural disasters such as hurricanes, tornadoes, and floods, after
7 school shootings, and in public emergencies, recovery must be prioritized as a long-term
8 process, rather than an immediate response only; and
9 WHEREAS, states, school districts, and postsecondary institutions have focused on
10 crisis prevention and management, but may not have the capacity to provide sustained
11 counseling support for their students, teachers, communities, and even their own
12 counselors during the recovery stage; and
13 WHEREAS, rural school districts and institutions in particular tend to have fewer
14 counselors and limited access to additional counseling resources; and
15 WHEREAS, school counselors are often expected to respond to student needs after
16 tragedy, even as they themselves grapple with the emotional toll, underscoring the need
17 for external support for the entire school community; and
18 WHEREAS, schools and institutions affected by crisis may require at least a year of
19 dedicated support to fully recover; and
20 WHEREAS, recovery efforts can strain resources that are already stretched thin,
21 given that a National Center for Education Statistics study showed that less than half of
22 public schools surveyed believe that their school is equipped to provide mental health
23 services to all students in need; and
24 WHEREAS, recovery is an extended healing process for students and adults alike,
25 and having additional counselors come to the aid of a school or institution in extreme
26 need supports the healing process of all people in the community, including teachers and
27 counselors; and
