1 WHEREAS, specialized training for counselors is essential to ensure they have
2 received psychological first aid training and provide counseling that aligns with the
3 unique needs of an educational environment; and
4 WHEREAS, research shows that students who receive adequate support after a
5 crisis are more likely to succeed academically, remain in school, and contribute positively
6 to society; and
7 WHEREAS, the Southern Regional Education Board (SREB), with its 75-year
8 history of partnering with states to improve education, is uniquely equipped to lead this
9 effort because of its ability to mobilize key education and policymaking stakeholders at
10 all levels; and
11 WHEREAS, SREB will cover the cost of a coordinator to operate the network, as
12 well as travel costs for network counselors during training and deployment; and
13 WHEREAS, SREB has secured funding for the first two years of training for a pool
14 of counselors from each SREB state; and
15 WHEREAS, the Kentucky General Assembly is aware that SREB will ask states for
16 $10,000 in additional funding in two years to sustain training of counselors;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
19 Kentucky, the House of Representatives concurring therein:
20 Section 1. To meet the urgent need for a coordinated, region-wide effort to
21 provide consistent long-term counseling capacity that is ready to deploy immediately
22 after a crisis is managed, the Kentucky General Assembly supports the mission of the
23 Southern Regional Education Board (SREB) Crisis Recovery Support Network. The
24 SREB, in close collaboration with governors’ offices, state education agencies, local
25 school districts, and postsecondary institutions, will complement existing school and
26 district crisis management efforts by focusing on long-term healing and psychological
27 resilience by deploying counselors with specialized training to schools in extreme need.
